          "rationale": "Workers' compensation is elective for private Texas employers, but a venue that chooses not to carry coverage (a non-subscriber) with non-exempt employees must file the DWC Form-005 non-subscriber notice - within 30 days of its first hire and again each year between February 1 and April 30 (Tex. Labor Code 406.004; the annual window is stated on the form). A non-subscriber also owes the separate employee-notice and workplace-posting duty (406.005).",
          "userAction": "If the venue does not carry workers' compensation, confirm it files the annual DWC Form-005 non-subscriber notice (by April 30 each year) and posts the employee coverage notice.",
          "notes": "Annual filing window opens February 1 and closes April 30; the fixed date models the April 30 deadline. Applicability keys on carriesWorkersComp = false (the non-subscriber election)."
        }
      ]
